{
    "id": 1039110,
    "name": "Ensure initializing cryptographic key generators (JEE)",
    "href": "AIP/quality-rules/1039110",
    "critical": true,
    "severity": 20,
    "maxWeight": 7,
    "extension": {
        "name": "com.castsoftware.jeerules",
        "href": "AIP/extensions/com.castsoftware.jeerules"
    },
    "associatedValueName": "Number of violation occurrences",
    "description": "This rules reports :\n  - usage of the KeyGenerator class without calling the init() method\n  - usage of the KeyPairGenerator class without calling the initialize() method\n\nIt is focused on Java's standard cryptographic API, provided by the Java Cryptography Architecture (JCA), part of the JDK.",
    "output": "Associated to each violation, the following information is provided:\n- The number of violation occurrences\n- Bookmarks for violation occurrences found in the source code",
    "rationale": "Using default parameters when generating keys can result in weaker encryption than advertised by the algorithm.",
    "reference": "CWE-325: Missing Cryptographic Step\nhttps://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/325.html\n\nOWASP Top 10:2021 - A02:2021 - Cryptographic Failures\nhttps://owasp.org/Top10/A02_2021-Cryptographic_Failures/",
    "remediation": "Explicitly set the recommended parameters for the cryptographic algorithm you are using (for instance a 2048-bit key for the RSA algorithm).",
    "remediationSample": "KeyPairGenerator keyPairGenerator = KeyPairGenerator.getInstance(\"RSA\");\nkeyPairGenerator.initialize(2048);  // FIXED\nKeyPair keyPair = keyPairGenerator.generateKeyPair();",
    "sample": "KeyPairGenerator keyPairGenerator = KeyPairGenerator.getInstance(\"RSA\");\n// Missing call to keyPairGenerator.initialize()\nKeyPair keyPair = keyPairGenerator.generateKeyPair();  // VIOLATION",
    "total": "Number of Java artifacts",
    "alternativeName": "Avoid using default parameters of key generators",
